				\begin{document}$$\hbox{H}^{+}$$\end{document}H+, e.g., norcamphor, a bicyclic ketone). The signals of this compound were clearly related to the BTH treatment and were highest from Golden Promise plants and lowest for Barke plants. To identify this compound further experiments involving trapping of the compound on absorption tubes followed by GC–MS analysis are necessary.

In addition, we observed the induction of monoterpene emissions (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
